{"text": "I have heard that on one occasion the Blessed One was staying near Sāvatthī at the Eastern Monastery, the palace of Migāra's mother. [1] And on that occasion, Visākhā, Migāra's mother, had some dealings with King Pasenadi Kosala that he did not settle as she had wished. So in the middle of the day she went to the Blessed One and, on arrival, having bowed down to him, sat to one side. As she was sitting there the Blessed One said to her, \"Well now, Visākhā, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?\"", "entities": [["PERSON", "Blessed One"], ["GPE", "Sāvatthī"], ["LOC", "Eastern Monastery"], ["PERSON", "Visākhā"], ["PERSON", "King Pasenadi Kosala"]]}
