{"text": "I have heard that on one occasion the Blessed One was staying near Sāvatthī at the Eastern Monastery, the palace of Migāra's mother. And on that occasion a dear and beloved grandson of Visākhā, Migāra's mother, had died. So Visākhā, Migāra's mother — her clothes wet, her hair wet — went to the Blessed One in the middle of the day and, on arrival, having bowed down to him, sat to one side. As she was sitting there the Blessed One said to her: \"Why have you come here, Visākhā — your clothes wet, your hair wet — in the middle of the day?\"", "entities": [["PERSON", "Blessed One"], ["GPE", "Sāvatthī"], ["LOC", "Eastern Monastery"], ["PERSON", "Visākhā"]]}
