{"text": "If, Vyagghapajja, a householder with little income were to lead an extravagant life, there would be those who say — 'This person enjoys his property like one who eats wood-apple.' [6] If, Vyagghapajja, a householder with a large income were to lead a wretched life, there would be those who say — 'This person will die like a starveling.'", "entities": [["PERSON", "Vyagghapajja"]]}
{"text": "In have heard that on one occasion the Blessed One was staying near Rājagaha on Vulture Peak mountain, not long after Devadatta had left. Referring to Devadatta , the Blessed One addressed the monks:", "entities": [["PERSON", "Blessed One"], ["GPE", "Rājagaha"], ["LOC", "Vulture Peak mountain"], ["PERSON", "Devadatta"]]}
