{"text": "It occurs to them: 'This Citta the householder is virtuous, of admirable character. If he should wish: \"In the future, may I become a king, a wheel-turning monarch!\" — then, as he is virtuous, this wish of his would succeed because of the purity of his virtue. A righteous one, he will wield righteous power.' [1] Seeing this compelling reason, they assembled and said: 'Make a wish, householder: \"In the future, may I become a king, a wheel-turning monarch!\"' And I said to them: 'Even that is inconstant; even that is impermanent; one must abandon even that when one passes on.'", "entities": [["PERSON", "Citta"]]}
{"text": "Last night, monks, a certain devata in the far extreme of the night, her extreme radiance lighting up the entirety of Jeta's Grove, came to me and, on arrival, bowed down to me and stood to one side.", "entities": [["LOC", "Jeta's Grove"]]}
