{"text": "Now, during the following Rains Retreat, Ven. Anuruddha stayed right there in the Eastern Bamboo Park among the Cetis. Dwelling alone, secluded, heedful, ardent, & resolute, he in no long time reached & remained in the supreme goal of the holy life for which clansmen rightly go forth from home into homelessness, knowing & realizing it for himself in the here & now. He knew: \"Birth is ended, the holy life fulfilled, the task done. There is nothing further for the sake of this world.\" And thus Ven. Anuruddha became another one of the arahants. Then, on attaining arahantship, he uttered this verse:", "entities": [["LOC", "Bamboo Park"], ["NORP", "Cetis"]]}
